OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, David Barton's fields on his farm in   
OL,6, Gloucestershire should be green and    
OL,7, full of grazing cattle.                
OL,9,FInstead the grass has turned yellow,   
OL,10,Fthe land is bone-dry, and many of the  
OL,11,Fcrops that feed his cows have died.    
OL,13,F"Every day that it doesn't rain, every 
OL,14,Fday that it's hot and dry, the pressure
OL,15,Fmounts," he says.                      
OL,17,FAs England and Wales enter a heatwave  
OL,18,Fforecast to last until Sunday, these   
OL,19,Fare challenging times for farmers.     
